# HCDE 530 Project Rules

This repo is for course assignments with small Python scripts, CSV files, and simple HTML pages.

## Directory Structure
Keep this section current as the project changes.

```text
Week 2/
├── .cursorrules
├── dashboard.html
├── demo_responses.csv
└── demo_word_count.py
```

## Coding Style
- Prefer clear, beginner-friendly code over clever one-liners.
- Keep functions small and give variables descriptive names.
- Add short comments only where logic is not obvious.
- Preserve existing file and naming conventions unless asked to refactor.

## Python Files
- Follow PEP 8 basics (spacing, naming, readable line lengths).
- Use simple, explicit data processing steps.
- Add basic error handling for file operations when practical.
- Print outputs in a readable format for class demos.

## CSV/Data Handling
- Do not modify source CSV data unless explicitly requested.
- Treat headers as authoritative and avoid hard-coding assumptions beyond known columns.
- When showing summaries, include counts/averages and label metrics clearly.

## HTML Dashboards
- Keep dashboards self-contained and easy to run locally.
- Favor vanilla HTML/CSS/JS unless a library is explicitly requested.
- Include clear instructions for local serving when browser file restrictions may apply.

## Git Workflow
- Make small, focused commits with clear messages.
- Do not commit secrets, credentials, or environment files.
- Confirm branch status before push and explain push/pull steps clearly when asked.

## Rule Maintenance
- When files/folders are added, renamed, moved, or removed, update the `Directory Structure` section in this file in the same change.
- Keep the structure concise and focused on important project files.
